item.title: 汽车需求疲软，芯片制造商 Wolfspeed 预计营收低于预期，股价下挫
item.description: Wolfspeed 公司周三预测的季度收入低于预期，并表示将因计划关闭一家工厂而计提 1.74 亿美元的重组费用，因为这家芯片制造商正在应对汽车客户的低迷需求。【原文：Wolfspeed forecast quarterly revenue below estimates on Wednesday and said it would book $174 million in restructuring charges for the planned closure of a facility, as the chipmaker deals with sluggish demand from automotive customers.】

item.title: 由于大片减少，AMC 娱乐公司收入下降
item.description: AMC 娱乐公司周三报告称，受好莱坞电影公司大片上映数量减少的影响，其连锁影院第三季度收入下降，上座率下降。【原文：AMC Entertainment on Wednesday reported a fall in third-quarter revenue and saw a decline in attendance at its theater chain, hurt by fewer blockbuster releases from Hollywood studios.】

item.title: 产量增加，马拉松石油公司第三季度利润超出预期
item.description: 美国页岩油生产商马拉松石油公司（Marathon Oil）周三公布的第三季度利润超出华尔街预期，主要得益于产量增加和石油需求的恢复性增长。【原文：U.S. shale producer Marathon Oil beat Wall Street estimates for third-quarter profit on Wednesday, helped by higher production and resilient demand for oil.】

item.title: 加拿大下令清盘 TikTok 加拿大业务，但仍可继续使用应用程序
item.description: 加拿大周三以国家安全风险为由，下令关闭 TikTok 在该国的业务，但补充说，政府并未阻止加拿大人访问这款短视频应用，也未阻止他们创建内容。【原文：Canada on Wednesday ordered the wind up of TikTok's business in the country citing national security risks, but added the government was not blocking Canadians' access to the short-video app or their ability to create content.】

item.title: 早间竞价为美国收益率、美元和通胀走高做好准备
item.description: 亚洲市场前瞻【原文：A look at the day ahead in Asian markets.】

item.title: 澳大利亚国民银行年度利润因竞争和成本压力而下降
item.description: 澳大利亚国民银行（National Australia Bank）周四公布的年度现金利润下降，基本符合市场预期，因为这家澳大利亚第二大银行正在努力应对激烈的住房贷款竞争和不断攀升的存款成本。【原文：National Australia Bank on Thursday reported a decline in annual cash profit, largely in line with market expectations, as the country's second-largest lender grappled with intense home-lending competition and escalating deposit costs.】

item.title: 大众美容需求放缓，Coty 年度利润低于预期
item.description: 科蒂公司（Coty）周三表示，由于美国和澳大利亚等主要市场对美容产品的需求疲软，抵消了香水业务的增长，预计全年利润将低于预期。【原文：Coty on Wednesday said it expects annual profit to come in at the low end of its forecast, as weak demand for beauty products in major markets such as the United States and Australia offset gains in the fragrance segment.】

item.title: Corteva 季度业绩不及预期
item.description: 受南美作物保护产品需求疲软的影响，美国农用化学品公司 Corteva 周三公布的第三季度利润未达预期。【原文：U.S. agrichemicals firm Corteva missed third-quarter profit estimates on Wednesday, hurt by weak demand for crop protection products in South America.】

item.title: Albemarle 第三季度因锂价下跌损失超过 10 亿美元
item.description: 全球最大的锂生产商 Albemarle 周四表示，由于电动汽车电池金属价格下跌 71%，该公司第三季度亏损超过 10 亿美元，并将削减资本预算。【原文：Albemarle , the world's largest lithium producer, said on Thursday it lost more than $1 billion in the third quarter and that it would slash its capital budget amid a 71% drop in prices for the electric vehicle battery metal.】

item.title: Match 集团预计季度收入低于预期，股价下跌
item.description: Match Group 周三预测第四季度营收低于华尔街预期，这表明由于客户削减可自由支配的开支，对其约会应用程序的需求疲软。【原文：Match Group forecast fourth-quarter revenue below Wall Street estimates on Wednesday, signaling weak demand for its dating apps as customers cut back on discretionary spending.】

item.title: 吉利德第三季度业绩超出华尔街预期，并上调业绩展望
item.description: 吉利德科学公司（Gilead Sciences）周三公布的第三季度财报大幅超出华尔街预期，销售额攀升了 7%，这使得该制药商上调了全年盈利展望。【原文：Gilead Sciences reported third-quarter financial results that handily beat Wall Street expectations on Wednesday as sales climbed 7%, leading the drugmaker to raise its outlook for full-year earnings.】

item.title: 人造肉需求疲软，Beyond Meat 下调年度收入预期上限
item.description: Beyond Meat 周三下调了年度收入预期的上限，原因是注重成本的消费者减少了对其昂贵的仿肉制品的消费，转而购买更便宜的替代品。【原文：Beyond Meat cut the top end of its annual revenue forecast on Wednesday, as cost-conscious consumers cut back spending on its expensive faux meat products and switched to cheaper alternatives.】

item.title: Take-Two Interactive 预测季度预订额低于预期
item.description: 本周三，Take-Two 互动软件公司（Take-Two Interactive Software）预测第三季度预订额低于华尔街预期，原因是消费者因通胀率长期走高和经济前景不明朗而削减了支出预算。【原文：Take-Two Interactive Software forecast third-quarter bookings below Wall Street expectations on Wednesday, as consumers cut spending budgets owing to higher-for-longer inflation and an uncertain economy.】

item.title: Bumble 第三季度营收超出预期
item.description: 周三，约会应用运营商 Bumble 第三季度营收超出预期，主要得益于付费订阅的增长，该公司股价在盘后交易中上涨了 9%。【原文：Dating app operator Bumble beat expectations for third-quarter revenue on Wednesday, helped by growth in paid subscriptions, sending its shares up 9% in extended trading.】

item.title: 化妆品需求回暖，精灵美容上调年度预期；股价上涨
item.description: 精灵美容公司（Elf Beauty）周三上调了对年度销售额和利润的预期，寄希望于在美国和海外以可承受的价格销售唇油和液体腮红等化妆品，这使得该公司股价在盘后交易中上涨了 18%。【原文：Elf Beauty raised its forecasts for annual sales and profit on Wednesday, betting on its efforts to sell cosmetics such as lip oil and liquid blush at affordable price points in the U.S. and abroad, sending the company's shares up 18% in extended trading.】

item.title: 物流和信贷成本导致 MercadoLibre 第三季度利润不及预期
item.description: 拉丁美洲电子商务巨头 MercadoLibre 周三公布，其第三季度净利润增长近 11%，但低于市场预期，原因是物流和信贷成本抵消了收入增长。【原文：Latin American e-commerce giant MercadoLibre on Wednesday posted a near 11% increase in its third-quarter net profit, missing market estimates as logistics and credit costs offfset revenue growth.】

item.title: Arm 第二季度营收和利润超出预期，股价下滑
item.description: 芯片设计公司 Arm Holdings 周三公布的第二季度营收和利润超出预期，部分原因是客户正在使用利润更高的下一代技术。【原文：Chip designer Arm Holdings , topped revenue and profit expectations for the second quarter on Wednesday, in part because customers are using a more profitable version of its next-generation technology.】

item.title: 高通公司业绩超预期，股价大涨 11
item.description: 芯片设计公司高通公司（Qualcomm）周三预计，由于受益于智能手机市场的复苏，该公司本季度的销售额和利润将超过华尔街的预期。【原文：Chip designer Qualcomm on Wednesday forecast sales and profit in the current quarter would exceed Wall Street estimates as the company benefits from a recovering smartphone market, and its shares rose 11% in extended trading.】

item.title: 马斯克与特朗普的影响力如何让他的公司富起来
item.description: 埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）支持唐纳德-特朗普（Donald Trump）决定性地胜出，成为第二任总统，这使这位亿万富翁企业家处于非同寻常的影响力地位，可以帮助他的公司获得有利的政府待遇。【原文：Elon Musk’s backing of Donald Trump’s decisive victory for a second presidency puts the billionaire entrepreneur in an extraordinary position of influence to help his companies secure favorable government treatment.】

item.title: 达能在芝加哥驳回依云微塑料诉讼案
item.description: 本周二，依云矿泉水的生产商达能公司赢得了一项诉讼的撤诉，该诉讼指控达能公司利用声称依云矿泉水 "纯天然 "的标签欺骗消费者，尽管这种水含有从瓶中渗出的微塑料。【原文：The maker of Evian spring water, Danone , won the dismissal of a lawsuit on Tuesday accusing it of defrauding consumers with labels that claim the water is "natural" even though it contains microplastics that seep from the bottle.】

item.title: Stellantis 将在俄亥俄州吉普车厂裁员 1,100 人
item.description: 吉普车制造商斯泰兰特公司表示，在努力提高北美业务效率和减少库存的同时，该公司将在俄亥俄州托莱多的吉普角斗士工厂裁员约 1100 人。【原文：Jeep-maker Stellantis said it is laying off about 1,100 employees at a Jeep Gladiator plant in Toledo, Ohio as it works to improve efficiency and reduce inventory across its North American operations.】

item.title: 特朗普胜选后公司债券利差略有收窄
item.description: 唐纳德-特朗普（Donald Trump）赢得总统大选后，企业债券市场利差周三略有收窄，因为市场正在权衡他重返白宫的利弊。【原文：Corporate bond market spreads tightened slightly on Wednesday after Donald Trump's presidential election victory, as the market weighs the pros and cons of his return to the White House.】

item.title: 特斯拉投资者因马斯克 2018 年的推文要求美国重新审判而败诉
item.description: 美国一家上诉法院周三维持了陪审团的判决，认定特斯拉公司首席执行官埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）及其公司没有责任，因为有人指控这位亿万富翁在 2018 年在社交媒体上发布消息称，他已 "获得资金 "将这家电动汽车公司私有化，从而误导了投资者。【原文：A U.S. appeals court on Wednesday upheld a jury's verdict clearing Tesla CEO Elon Musk and his company of liability over allegations they misled investors when the billionaire posted on social media in 2018 that he had "funding secured" to take the electric car company private.】

item.title: 高盛首席执行官祝贺特朗普大选获胜，呼吁团结一致
item.description: 高盛集团（Goldman Sachs）首席执行官大卫-所罗门（David Solomon）周三祝贺当选总统唐纳德-特朗普（Donald Trump）赢得大选，这与科技行业首席执行官们此前发表的言论不谋而合。【原文：Goldman Sachs CEO David Solomon on Wednesday congratulated President-elect Donald Trump on his election victory, echoing earlier comments from CEOs in the technology industry.】

item.title: 蓝湾和 Man Group 将重点转向特朗普领导下的银行、债券和石油交易
item.description: 在唐纳德-特朗普（Donald Trump）当选总统后，包括 BlueBay 和 Man Group 在内的对冲基金周三将目光转向了原油、美国国债、科技和美国银行。【原文：Hedge funds including BlueBay and Man Group were turning their attentions to crude oil, U.S. Treasuries, tech and U.S. banks on Wednesday, after Donald Trump was elected president.】

item.title: Blackstone Real Estate 将以 40 亿美元的交易将 Retail Opportunity 私有化
item.description: Blackstone Real Estate 周三签订协议，以全现金交易方式将 Retail Opportunity Investments Corp 私有化，包括债务在内的交易价值约为 40 亿美元。【原文：Blackstone Real Estate on Wednesday entered into an agreement to take Retail Opportunity Investments Corp private in an all-cash transaction valued at about $4 billion, including debt.】

item.title: 马萨诸塞州选民允许优步和 Lyft 司机成立工会
item.description: 马萨诸塞州选民周二批准了一项允许共享汽车司机成立工会的投票措施，成为美国第一个允许 Uber 和 Lyft 等应用程序公司的司机成立工会的州。【原文：Massachusetts voters on Tuesday approved a ballot measure that would allow ride-share drivers to unionize, becoming the first U.S. state to allow drivers for app-based companies like Uber and Lyft to do so.】

item.title: 欧洲央行行长维勒鲁瓦特朗普当选意味着世界经济面临更多风险
item.description: 欧洲央行决策者、法国央行行长弗朗索瓦-维勒鲁瓦-德-加尔豪（Francois Villeroy de Galhau）周三表示，唐纳德-特朗普当选下一任美国总统意味着全球经济将面临更多下行风险。【原文：The election of Donald Trump as the next U.S. president means there will be more downside risks to the global economy, ECB policymaker and French central bank head Francois Villeroy de Galhau said on Wednesday.】

item.title: 赛峰集团任命飞机发动机、电气与动力部门新任首席执行官
item.description: 法国喷气发动机制造商赛峰集团周三表示，已任命Stephane Cueille为其飞机发动机部门首席执行官，接替Jean-Paul Alary的职位将于2025年前几个月生效。【原文：Safran has appointed Stephane Cueille as CEO of its Aircraft Engines unit, replacing Jean-Paul Alary effective in the first few months of 2025, the French jet engine maker said on Wednesday.】

item.title: 独家报道文件显示：欧盟监管机构调查威士卡和万事达卡收费是否损害零售商利益
item.description: 路透社看到的一份欧盟文件显示，欧盟反垄断监管机构正在调查威士卡和万事达卡收取的费用是否对零售商产生了负面影响。【原文：EU antitrust regulators are investigating whether the fees charged by Visa and Mastercard have a negative impact on retailers, an EU document seen by Reuters showed.】
